{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.33",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 33 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:1",
      "text": "Wherefore, Job, I pray thee, hear my speeches, and hearken to all my words.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:2",
      "text": "Behold, now I have opened my mouth, my tongue hath spoken in my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:3",
      "text": "My words shall be of the uprightness of my heart: and my lips shall utter knowledge clearly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:4",
      "text": "The Spirit of God hath made me, and the breath of the Almighty hath given me life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:5",
      "text": "If thou canst answer me, set thy words in order before me, stand up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:6",
      "text": "Behold, I am according to thy wish in God’s stead: I also am formed out of the clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:7",
      "text": "Behold, my terror shall not make thee afraid, neither shall my hand be heavy upon thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:8",
      "text": "Surely thou hast spoken in mine hearing, and I have heard the voice of thy words, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:9",
      "text": "I am clean without transgression, I am innocent; neither is there iniquity in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:10",
      "text": "Behold, he findeth occasions against me, he counteth me for his enemy,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:11",
      "text": "He putteth my feet in the stocks, he marketh all my paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:12",
      "text": "Behold, in this thou art not just: I will answer thee, that God is greater than man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:13",
      "text": "Why dost thou strive against him? for he giveth not account of any of his matters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:14",
      "text": "For God speaketh once, yea twice, yet man perceiveth it not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:15",
      "text": "In a dream, in a vision of the night, when deep sleep falleth upon men, in slumberings upon the bed;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:16",
      "text": "Then he openeth the ears of men, and sealeth their instruction,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:17",
      "text": "That he may withdraw man from his purpose, and hide pride from man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:18",
      "text": "He keepeth back his soul from the pit, and his life from perishing by the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:19",
      "text": "He is chastened also with pain upon his bed, and the multitude of his bones with strong pain:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:20",
      "text": "So that his life abhorreth bread, and his soul dainty meat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:21",
      "text": "His flesh is consumed away, that it cannot be seen; and his bones that were not seen stick out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:22",
      "text": "Yea, his soul draweth near unto the grave, and his life to the destroyers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:23",
      "text": "If there be a messenger with him, an interpreter, one among a thousand, to shew unto man his uprightness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:24",
      "text": "Then he is gracious unto him, and saith, Deliver him from going down to the pit: I have found a ransom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:25",
      "text": "His flesh shall be fresher than a child’s: he shall return to the days of his youth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:26",
      "text": "He shall pray unto God, and he will be favourable unto him: and he shall see his face with joy: for he will render unto man his righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:27",
      "text": "He looketh upon men, and if any say, I have sinned, and perverted that which was right, and it profited me not;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:28",
      "text": "He will deliver his soul from going into the pit, and his life shall see the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:29",
      "text": "Lo, all these things worketh God oftentimes with man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:30",
      "text": "To bring back his soul from the pit, to be enlightened with the light of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:31",
      "text": "Mark well, O Job, hearken unto me: hold thy peace, and I will speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:32",
      "text": "If thou hast any thing to say, answer me: speak, for I desire to justify thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.33.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:33",
      "text": "If not, hearken unto me: hold thy peace, and I shall teach thee wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
